=== Contrast with Adult Prognosis

Adult ME/CFS has dramatically worse outcomes (see Chapter @ch:disease-course and Section @sec:adult-recovery-evidence for comprehensive analysis):

    - Recovery: Only 5% (median across studies)
    - Improvement: $lt.eq$22%
    - Most adults with ME/CFS have lifelong illness

The stark difference between pediatric and adult outcomes suggests that biological factors related to developmental plasticity, or barriers to recovery present in adults but absent in children (continued work demands, financial pressures), may significantly influence trajectory. For analysis of why adult recovery rates may be underestimated and the evidence limitations affecting these statistics, see Section @sec:adult-recovery-evidence.

